Breast_Composition: predominantly fibro fatty breast parenchyma (ACR A).
Findings:
a small area of architectural distortion with foci of microcalcifications seen in the upper quadrant of the breast 
suggest low suspicious lesion (BIRADS 4a).
benign-looking calcifications are seen in the retroareolar and lower periareolar region. 
skin, nipple, and pectoral muscle appear normal.
benign-looking axillary adenopathy.
